    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12659#pullrequestreview-3850834365\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Ah this was part of a recent refactor where these calls can't be skipped so they can't just return <code>Ok(())</code> and work correctly. Can you add calls to <code>self.enter_call_not_concurrent()</code> and <code>self.exit_call_not_concurrent()</code> in the disabled case? </p>\n<p>For a test for this, can you add a test with concurrency_supoprt disabled and a host call with a <code>borrow&lt;T&gt;</code> resource is done? I think it should panic and/or cause problems with the PR as-is, but if not I can help whip up a more involved test.</p>\n</blockquote>",
